1
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,120
<i>This is Berk.</i>

2
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:35,800
<i>So far off the map
that it might as well not exist.</i>

3
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,360
<i>My village</i>

4
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>in a word: Sturdy.</i>

5
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:42,440
<i>It's been here for generations</i>

6
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:44,320
<i>but every single building is new.</i>

7
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,840
<i>The air is crisp, the water is clean</i>

8
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:48,640
<i>and the views are
nothing to complain about.</i>

9
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:51,800
<i>The only downsides are the pests.</i>

10
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:02,600
<i>You see, most places have
mice or mosquitoes.</i>

11
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,400
<i>We have...</i>

12
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:10,720
Dragons.

13
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:16,840
<i>Most people would leave.</i>

14
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,400
<i>Not us.</i>

15
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,000
<i>We're Vikings.</i>

16
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,480
<i>We don't run from fights.
We start them.</i>

17
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:24,120
- Hey! Hiccup!
- Evening!

18
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,320
- Go home!
- I will just as soon as I...

19
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,400
You're in the way again!

20
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,000
Hiccup, play dead!

21
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:35,560
<i>You see, dragons have been
a bit of a problem.</i>

22
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:38,880
<i>Here and, well, everywhere.</i>

23
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:41,200
<i>So we decided
to take the fight to them.</i>

24
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,720
<i>How's that working out for us?</i>

25
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:51,800
What are you doing?

26
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,920
What is he doing out again?

27
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,800
Get inside. Go on.

28
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,960
<i>That's Stoick the Vast</i>

29
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:00,160
<i>chief of the tribe.</i>

30
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,880
<i>They say when he was a baby</i>

31
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:05,320
<i>he popped a dragon's head
clean off its shoulders.</i>

32
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:06,960
<i>Do I believe it?</i>

33
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:11,080
<i>- Yes, I do.</i>
- What have we got?

34
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:14,520
Gronckles, Nadders,
Zipplebacks, Skrills.

35
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,640
Snorti spotted a Monstrous Nightmare.

36
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,720
Any Night Furies?

37
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,800
None so far, Chief.

38
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:19,880
Good.

39
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,320
- Follow me.
- Right, Chief.

40
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,320
Come on, you wretches!

41
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,400
You heard him. Come on, lads.

42
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,840
Oh. Out again?

43
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,000
Just pretend I'm not even here.

44
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,920
I'll be in and out
before you can say...

45
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,400
Not so fast.

46
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,120
Come on, please.

47
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,800
<i>The meathead with attitude
and interchangeable hands is Gobber.</i>

48
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,160
Here. Go on.

49
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,160
<i>I've been his apprentice
ever since I was little.</i>

50
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,600
I'm keeping my eye on you.

51
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,160
I'm not even supposed to be out here.

52
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,440
Since when did that ever stop ya?

53
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,440
- Guard the food stores.
- Aye, Chief.

54
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,400
- Protect the livestock.
- Aye, Stoick.

55
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,320
And keep an ear out for Night Furies.

56
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,240
Hammer.

57
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,440
Fire brigade!

58
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,920
<i>Ah, the fire brigade.</i>

59
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,520
<i>Berk's cool kids.</i>

60
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,520
<i>They get to be out in the action.</i>

61
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,120
Guys, out of the way!

62
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,440
<i>But they're nothing
without their captain</i>

63
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,520
<i>the shining star of our generation.</i>

64
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,920
<i>Amazing without even trying.</i>

65
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,000
<i>The one that smokes them all.</i>

66
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,920
<i>Astrid.</i>

67
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,000
What?

68
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,720
Shouldn't you be in bed?

69
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,400
Come on, back to work.

70
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,240
You know, I need to get out there.

71
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,800
Show my stuff, make my mark.

72
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,600
You've made plenty of marks,
all in the wrong places.

73
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,680
Give me two minutes.

74
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:12,840
I'll take down a dragon.

75
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,120
My life will get infinitely better.

76
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,936
I might even get a girlfriend.

77
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:18,400
There's a Zippleback behind you!

78
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,480
Astrid?

79
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,360
But she's a real Viking.

80
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,560
You can't wield a hammer.

81
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,720
You can't swing an axe.

82
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,240
You can't even throw one of these.

83
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,680
See, but this,
this will throw it for me.

84
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,120
- Another one.
- It's fully redesigned. It's...

85
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,800
It's...

86
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,320
double-barreled.

87
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,120
You see, this right here

88
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,376
- this is what I'm talking about.
- Okay, this is a mild cal...

89
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,680
mild calibration issue.

90
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,936
If you ever want to get out there
and start fighting dragons

91
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,240
you've gotta stop all of...

92
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,120
all of this.

93
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,320
You just gestured to all of me.

94
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,400
Yeah. Stop being all of you.

95
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,440
Oh, yeah.

96
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,880
You, sir, are playing
a dangerous game

97
00:04:58,280 --> 00:04:59,400
keeping this contained?

98
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,440
There will be consequences.

99
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:04,800
Well, I will take my chances.

100
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,320
Sword, sharpen. Now.

101
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,240
<i>One day, I'll get out there.</i>

102
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:15,920
<i>Because killing a dragon
is everything around here.</i>

103
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,600
<i>Gronckles are tough.</i>

104
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:21,400
<i>Taking one down
would at least get me noticed.</i>

105
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,240
<i>A Zippleback?</i>

106
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,520
<i>Exotic, exciting.</i>

107
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:31,080
<i>Two heads, twice the status.</i>

108
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,080
<i>Lopping off a Nadder's head</i>

109
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,760
<i>would definitely show them I belong.</i>

110
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,080
Come on, lads!

111
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,520
They found the sheep.

112
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,560
Then let loose
with everything we've got.

113
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:47,640
Chief!

114
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:54,320
<i>And then there's
the Monstrous Nightmare.</i>

115
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,480
Reload!

116
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,680
<i>Only the best Vikings go after those.</i>

117
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,720
<i>But the ultimate prize</i>

118
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,320
<i>is the dragon that
no one has ever seen.</i>

119
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:12,160
<i>- We call it the...</i>
- Night Fury!

120
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,240
Jump!

121
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,760
And we've got a Night Fury.

122
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:20,920
Never steals food.

123
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,800
Never shows itself.

124
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,400
And never misses.

125
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,800
Time for old Gobber to take over.

126
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,480
Stay put here.

127
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,160
Here. I'm serious.

128
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,520
<i>No one has ever killed a Night Fury.</i>

129
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,440
Attack!

130
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,400
<i>That's why I'm going to be the first.</i>

131
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,960
You again? Get back inside!

132
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,640
- I'll make a point of it.
- Gonna get yourself killed, Hiccup!

133
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,200
I know! Sorry.

134
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,200
Gobber!

135
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:54,720
Here, give me that.

136
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,240
Mind yourself!

137
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,920
This Nadder still has
some fire in it.

138
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,400
Come on.

139
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:19,240
Give me something to shoot at.
Give me something to shoot at.

140
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,200
Come on, show yourself.

141
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,520
I hit it.

142
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,720
I hit it!

143
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,320
Did anybody see that?

144
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,440
Except for you.

145
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,120
Oh, Gods.

146
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,800
Spitelout, do not let that escape.

147
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:58,920
Thanks a lot.

148
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,600
You're all out.

149
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,720
Let's see what else you're made of.

150
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:46,120
Aye, that's what I thought.

151
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,920
<i>Oh, and there's
one more thing to know.</i>

152
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,600
Look out!

153
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,120
Sorry, Dad.

154
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:09,560
Watch out!

155
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,120
Okay, but I hit a Night Fury.

156
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,720
Dad, this isn't like any other time.

157
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,000
I mean, I really hit one.

158
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:30,960
Aye, a dragon no one's ever seen.

159
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,160
Because it uses night
as its camouflage.

160
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,136
If you squint, you can see
it blotting out the stars.

161
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,320
That's how I shot it down.

162
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,400
Stop!

163
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,480
Stop.

164
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,720
Every time you step outside,
disaster happens.

165
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,600
Can you not see
that I have bigger problems?

166
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,200
Winter is almost here

167
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,440
and I have an entire village to feed.

168
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:54,520
Between you and me, the village
could do with a little less feeding.

169
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,120
This isn't a joke, Hiccup!

170
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,200
Why can't you follow
the simplest orders?

171
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,920
Because I can't stop myself.

172
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:05,920
Okay? I see a dragon,
and I have to just kill it.

173
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,560
You know, it's who I am.

174
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,800
You are many things, son

175
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:15,120
but a dragon killer
is not one of them.

176
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,560
Get back to the house.

177
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,120
Make sure he stays there.

178
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,960
How much can one person mess up?

179
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:27,520
Anyone else would have been
booted off the island by now.

180
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,960
I guess being son of the chief
has its privileges.

181
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,160
If not for the chief, though...

182
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:38,400
Anyway, my dad's
super proud of me, so...

183
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:41,841
- Dad, I was just talking...
- Don't talk to me in public.

184
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,736
You know, I really did hit one.

185
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,760
Course you did, Hiccup.

186
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,240
He never listens.

187
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,560
Well, that runs in the family.

188
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,120
And when he does

189
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,720
it's always
with some disappointed scowl

190
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,160
like somebody forgot
the meat in the stew.

191
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:57,640
I've seen that look.

192
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:01,000
Oi. You're thinking
about this all wrong, eh.

193
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,920
It's not so much what you look like.

194
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,240
It's what's inside of you
he can't stand.

195
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,800
Thank you for summing that up.

196
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:12,200
W... Wait. The point is

197
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,120
stop trying so hard
to be something you're not.

198
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,000
I just wanna be one of you guys.

199
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,360
I know you do.

200
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,320
No one said it would be easy!

201
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,320
But may I remind you

202
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,080
we are all descendants

203
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:05,360
of the finest dragon fighters

204
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:08,120
from everywhere Vikings have traveled

205
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,960
who gathered here because they knew

206
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:13,240
that we were within spitting distance

207
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:15,520
of a key dragon's nest.

208
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,760
If we can just take it

209
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:21,160
we can wipe out the devils for good.

210
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,280
Take it?

211
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,840
- We can't even find it.
- Exactly.

212
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:27,400
This nest is starting to sound
more and more like a fairy tale.

213
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,720
We're exhausted.

214
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,640
And what do we have
to show for it, eh?

215
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,840
- Nothing!
- We have purpose.

216
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,600
Oh, come on.

217
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:37,920
We are the warriors of Berk

218
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,120
the roughest, toughest tribe
this side of the sun.

219
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,800
No?

220
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:45,920
Phlegma.

221
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:51,080
We watched you take down
a Zippleback single-handedly.

222
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,496
I mean, sure, you lost
your leg in the process

223
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,920
but you came out on top, didn't you?

224
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,400
- Well...
- Yes, you did.

225
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:00,920
Retcha, your people came
from the Far East.

226
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:04,600
Fungi, yours all the way
from... from the Silk Road.

227
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:08,840
Loogi, your people came
from the sun baked coasts of Bláland.

228
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:10,040
And look at us.

229
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:12,120
We're still here.
We're still fighting.

230
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,520
We're still watching
each other's backs.

231
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:18,120
So are we really gonna
pack up and go home

232
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:22,400
while these bloody beasts are
still a threat to all of our lands?

233
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,880
Is that who we are?

234
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:25,960
No.

235
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:31,720
- Is it?
- No!

236
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,120
Is it?

237
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,920
No, Chief, I guess not.

238
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,000
That's what I thought.

239
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,560
Elder Gothi

240
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,160
give us a sign.

241
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:47,920
Do we stand a chance of finding
the nest before the ice sets in?

242
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,000
Then that's all I need.

243
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:13,400
Back into the fog we go.

244
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,040
All right, everyone.

245
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,520
Prepare the ships!

246
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,600
Let's go!

247
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:31,800
Do I take my bucket hand
for when they burn our ships

248
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,600
or my swimming hand
for when they sink them?

249
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:41,000
Not so fast, Gobber.

250
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,640
I don't have time
to train this year's recruits

251
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,200
so you'll do it.

252
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,000
The old rite of passage.

253
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,000
Hiccup's just come of age, hasn't he?

254
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:52,680
I meant the others.

255
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,000
Yeah, so while I'm busy,
he'll cover the stall.

256
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,000
Molten steel, razor-sharp blades

257
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,160
lots of time on his hands.

258
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,520
What could possibly go wrong?

259
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,520
What am I gonna do with him, Gobber?

260
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,720
Stick him in training.

261
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,560
No. I'm serious.

262
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,640
Yeah, so am I.

263
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:10,200
The kid wants this
more than anything.

264
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:11,600
Believe it or not

265
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:14,240
that young man actually wants
to make you proud.

266
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:15,920
But he's got a mind of his own.

267
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,880
Gets that from his mother.

268
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,880
Look what happened to her.

269
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,480
Yeah, 'cause Valka was
the stubborn one.

270
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:23,400
- See, when I was a boy,
- Oh, here we go.

271
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,720
I... I followed orders.
Right? I worked hard.

272
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:28,600
Because I believed
in what a... a Viking could do.

273
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,320
Crush mountains

274
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,920
level forests, tame seas.

275
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:37,080
I knew what I was
and what I had to become.

276
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:38,920
Hiccup is...

277
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,840
He's not that boy.

278
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:45,200
What chance does he have
of following in my footsteps?

279
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,200
Yeah.

280
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,200
You can't stop him, Stoick.

281
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,520
You can only prepare him.

282
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,320
Because the truth is

283
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,520
we aren't always gonna
be around to protect him.

284
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,800
He's gonna get out there again.

285
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,720
He's probably out there now.

286
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,600
How could I lose an entire dragon?

287
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:38,320
I did it.

288
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,120
I did it!

289
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,000
Why couldn't you have been dead?

290
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,920
Now I have to kill you.

291
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:50,840
Hiccup?

292
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:52,800
Dad.

293
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:57,720
Look, I need to talk to you, Dad.

294
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:02,200
I need to speak with you, too, son.

295
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,856
- I've decided I don't want
- I think it's time you learn

296
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,056
- to fight dragons.
- To fight dragons.

297
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,080
- What?
- What?

298
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,840
- Well, you go first.
- No... no. You... You go first.

299
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,520
You get your wish.

300
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,280
Dragon Training.

301
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,680
Start in the morning.

302
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,960
Oh, man, I really
should've gone first.

303
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,400
You know, 'cause I was thinking

304
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:25,400
we have a surplus
of dragon-fighting Vikings

305
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:27,016
but do we have
enough bread-making Vikings

306
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,080
- or...
- You'll need this.

307
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:29,760
Dad...

308
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,800
I don't wanna fight dragons.

309
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,240
Come on. Yes, you do.

310
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,120
No, let me rephrase.

311
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,800
I can't kill dragons.

312
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,040
But you will.

313
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,600
No, I'm very extra sure that I won't.

314
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,000
It's time, Hiccup.

315
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,120
Can you not hear me?

316
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,920
Can you not hear me?

317
00:20:57,120 --> 00:21:00,120
The Trial of Flame is
where Vikings are made

318
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,400
where heroes are forged

319
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:05,000
where future chiefs are born.

320
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,600
I'm none of those things.

321
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,240
I'm not like you, Dad.

322
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,400
Listen.

323
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:24,120
When you carry this axe

324
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,000
you carry all of us with you

325
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,920
which means you walk like us

326
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:32,000
you talk like us, you think like us.

327
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,520
No more of this.

328
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:38,320
You just gestured to all of me.

329
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:40,520
Deal?

330
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:41,656
This conversation is feeling

331
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,120
- very one-sided.
- Deal?

332
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:47,120
Deal.

333
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,400
Good.

334
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,120
Train hard.

335
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,480
I'll be back.

336
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,400
Probably.

337
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,320
And I'll be here.

338
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,600
Maybe.

339
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:21,400
Welcome to the Trial of Flame.

340
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:37,200
The moment
we've all been waiting for.

341
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,960
I just got to pick
a spot for my statue.

342
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:42,000
It's so much bigger from down here.

343
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:44,080
Can you guys believe
we're actually standing here?

344
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:47,240
This is where Chief Greybile slew
the Whispering Death.

345
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,720
Yeah, and it's where Chief Tuffnut
will slay everything else.

346
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,480
- Watch and learn.
- Man, I can't wait

347
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:53,400
to get some legendary war wounds.

348
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:56,120
Yeah, like a nasty gash
right across my face.

349
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,480
- Call me boring...
- Boring.

350
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:01,280
But I'm just excited to see
some real live dragons up close.

351
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:04,160
You know, I could do
without the permanent injuries and...

352
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,376
Oh, where's the glory in that?

353
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,280
Yeah, it's only fun
if you get a scar out of it.

354
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,480
I know, right?

355
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:12,280
Pain. Love it.

356
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:14,720
Oh, great. Who let him in?

357
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:17,280
I guess Daddy pulled
some strings, huh?

358
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:18,656
Aren't you two, like,
a little old to be here?

359
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:19,680
- Ouch.
- Wait

360
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:22,320
- what'd you say, whippersnapper?
- What'd you say? Say it again!

361
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,800
Yeah, touchy subject.

362
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,920
They've flunked Dragon Training
a few times.

363
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,000
It was four times, actually.

364
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:29,720
Yeah, and it's called
being held back.

365
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,600
As in too valuable to let go of.

366
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,120
Real sensitive, Hiccup.

367
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,320
Nice name, by the way.

368
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,200
Your name is Snotlout.

369
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,280
Exactly.

370
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:40,000
It's a manly Viking name.

371
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:41,840
Translates from the ancient texts

372
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,440
as "one who beateth the snot"

373
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,520
- "out of a... "
- Shut up.

374
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:45,920
Let's get started.

375
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,400
Bloody kids.

376
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:52,040
You are now the latest to join
this time-honored tradition.

377
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:54,440
Every toe biter born into our tribe

378
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,400
must one day survive this arena

379
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:59,000
if they ever hope to do battle
alongside the rest of us.

380
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:01,920
It will be grueling.

381
00:24:04,640 --> 00:24:07,360
And it will be very, very dangerous.

382
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:12,880
But whoever does best
will win the title of Top Slayer.

383
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:15,560
And with it...

384
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:18,800
And with it, the honor

385
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:22,200
of killing their first dragon
in front of the entire village.

386
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,520
There is no greater glory.

387
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:26,840
What?

388
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:29,040
Hiccup already killed a Night Fury

389
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:31,400
so does that, like, what,
disqualify him or...

390
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:32,920
Oh, ignore him.

391
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:34,760
You're skinny.

392
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:36,200
You're weak.

393
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,200
That'll make you less of a target.

394
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,400
They'll see you as slim pickings.

395
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,480
Not worth the effort.

396
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,920
They'll go after the more...

397
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,880
Viking-like teens instead.

398
00:24:48,280 --> 00:24:49,400
Behind these doors

399
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,320
are just a few of the many species
you will learn to fight.

400
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,800
The Deadly Nadder.

401
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,240
Attack, eight, armor, 16.

402
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:57,080
The Hideous Zippleback.

403
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,560
Plus 11 stealth, times two.

404
00:24:58,640 --> 00:24:59,920
The Monstrous Nightmare.

405
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,920
- Firepower, 15.
- The Terrible Terror.

406
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,920
- Attack, eight, venom, 12!
- Will you stop that?

407
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:06,400
You big bag of wool.

408
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:11,200
And finally, the gruesome Gronckle.

409
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,200
Jaw strength, eight.

410
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:17,720
Hey, big guy!

411
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:20,960
Aren't you gonna, like,
teach us something first?

412
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:22,400
I believe in learning on the job!

413
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:29,400
Today is all about defense!

414
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,360
If you get blasted, you're out!

415
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:33,720
Or, you know, dead.

416
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,696
So, what's the first thing
you're gonna need?

417
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,640
- A shield!
- Shield, yes. Go!

418
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,056
- Out of my way.
- That one's mine!

419
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:41,520
Shield is your most
important piece of equipment.

420
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:46,320
If you have to choose
between a weapon and a shield...

421
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,040
Just put it down.

422
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,560
Take the shield.

423
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,720
- Give it! Find your own shield!
- Mine, mine, mine!

424
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:58,320
Ruffnut, Tuffnut, you're out.

425
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:02,520
Shields are good
for another thing: Noise.

426
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:05,520
Make plenty of it
to throw off the dragon's aim.

427
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:11,320
Remember, all dragons have
a limited number of blasts.

428
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,000
How many does a Gronckle have?

429
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,720
- Six!
- Six, yes.

430
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,400
That's one for each of ya.

431
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,080
Although, interesting tidbit

432
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,400
rocks from different regions
vary in mineral comp...

433
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,880
What are you do...
What are you doing?

434
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,360
What are you doing? Get in there!

435
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,720
Fishlegs, you're out.

436
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:34,400
- Four shots left.
- Yeah.

437
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,480
We're pretty much gonna be
the stars of this thing.

438
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,280
Almost like we were meant
to be together.

439
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,880
It's an elimination game, genius.

440
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:41,200
There's only one Top Slayer.

441
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:46,040
Snotlout, you're done.

442
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:47,880
Three shots.

443
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:50,560
Looks like it's just you and me, huh?

444
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:52,080
Nope. Just me.

445
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,920
Hey! Eyes on me!

446
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,000
Yes.

447
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,800
Well done, Astrid.

448
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:05,920
Two shots left.

449
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,440
Oh, come on.

450
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,120
Hiccup, you're out.

451
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:13,520
- One shot left.
- Hey, watch it!

452
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:16,640
Hiccup!

453
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,080
End of lesson.

454
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,800
Back to bed, you overgrown sausage.

455
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:40,120
Remember, a dragon
will always, always...

456
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,000
go for the kill.

457
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,600
So, why didn't you?

458
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:03,400
Okay.

459
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,320
Let's review, shall we?

460
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:14,320
Where did Astrid go wrong
in the ring today?

461
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:16,120
I mistimed my somersault dive.

462
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,000
It was sloppy.
It threw off my reverse tumble.

463
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:19,840
- Yeah. We noticed.
- Hey.

464
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:21,640
Back off my girl.

465
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:23,376
All right? She's trying her best.

466
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:25,520
Yeah. Don't beat yourself up.
You'll get it.

467
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:27,520
Just follow my lead next time!

468
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:28,920
Astrid's right.

469
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:31,000
You've gotta be tough on yourselves.

470
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,200
All it takes is one weak link.

471
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:36,760
You made it, then?

472
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:40,920
You gotta start taking this seriously

473
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:43,440
because we are living
in a battleground.

474
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:46,240
And in case you haven't noticed,
the other side is winning.

475
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:48,320
You're gonna need
every advantage you can get.

476
00:30:48,520 --> 00:30:50,680
So, if you haven't done your homework

477
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,320
allow me to present to you...

478
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,000
The Book of Dragons.

479
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:03,240
Everything we know
about every dragon we know of.

480
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:07,160
Each of your tribes brought
their wisdom and experience

481
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,240
to these pages.

482
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,120
It's our most hallowed possession.

483
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,440
No dragon raids tonight

484
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:16,520
so study up.

485
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,240
You mean read?

486
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:21,320
I've read it like a hundred times.

487
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:24,360
There's a Scauldron that sprays
your face with boiling water.

488
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:26,600
And then there's another...

489
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,560
Why would I read words

490
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:31,560
when I can just kill the stuff
the words tell me stuff about?

491
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,200
Right? I mean, like,
I'm the kind of guy

492
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,720
that other guys write
word books about.

493
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:37,840
Boys!

494
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,256
Don't worry, though. I'm here

495
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:41,280
for all of your dragon-related
inquiries, okay?

496
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:44,800
Theories, stats.
I've even made cards...

497
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:47,560
You can ask me anything.

498
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:48,696
- Stop following me.
- Here.

499
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:49,760
How about now? Try me now.

500
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,000
Absolutely not.

501
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:00,360
So...

502
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:04,000
sounds like a gruesome,
grisly, good time, huh?

503
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:06,640
- Read it.
- You know...

504
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:10,440
maybe they're not as bad
as we think they are.

505
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:15,320
Are you actually insane,
or do you just act that way?

506
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:17,400
Is there... Is there a third option?

507
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:21,120
Wiping out dragons is why we're here.

508
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:23,400
It's why the best of our tribes
came together.

509
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:26,560
Because yes, dragons
are as bad as we think.

510
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,040
Yeah, I know. I'm just saying

511
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:30,440
maybe we're part of the problem.

512
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,600
You know, moving in on their lands

513
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:33,920
eating their food.

514
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:39,880
Wow.

515
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,400
You live in a different world,
don't you?

516
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,040
- What?
- Just coast by

517
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,400
taking it all for granted.

518
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:48,656
- Well, I don't think that...
- Never having to work for anything

519
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:50,040
never struggling to get a foot up.

520
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,440
Well, guess what?

521
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:54,000
I come from nothing.

522
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:57,800
No chief for a dad,
no handouts, no excuses.

523
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,456
I'm not afraid of hard work.
I'm willing to do

524
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:00,856
whatever it takes
to get the job done

525
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:03,040
which, in this case, means
wiping out the dragons

526
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,600
for the good of everyone.

527
