I was hoping for this.

798
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:50,160
- You were?
- Oh, yes.

799
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:53,080
And believe me, it only gets better.

800
01:00:53,160 --> 01:00:57,280
Just wait till you spill
a Nadder's guts for the first time.

801
01:00:57,360 --> 01:01:01,720
Or... Or mount your first
Gronckle head on a spear.

802
01:01:02,120 --> 01:01:03,360
What a feeling.

803
01:01:04,120 --> 01:01:06,120
You really had me going there, son.

804
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:10,040
All those years of the worst Viking

805
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:11,720
Berk has ever seen.

806
01:01:12,680 --> 01:01:14,200
Odin, it was rough.

807
01:01:14,280 --> 01:01:15,800
I almost gave up on you.

808
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:19,080
And all the while,
you were holding out on me.

809
01:01:19,880 --> 01:01:21,720
Thor almighty.

810
01:01:22,160 --> 01:01:23,216
Who would have thought that

811
01:01:23,240 --> 01:01:26,920
Dragon Training would have been
your place to shine, huh?

812
01:01:27,800 --> 01:01:29,520
You might even win Top Slayer.

813
01:01:30,320 --> 01:01:31,600
Just like your old man.

814
01:01:32,040 --> 01:01:33,040
Who knows?

815
01:01:34,000 --> 01:01:37,200
You know, actually,
with you doing so well in the ring...

816
01:01:37,840 --> 01:01:39,600
- I'm gonna... Okay.
- Sit.

817
01:01:39,680 --> 01:01:42,840
We finally have
something to talk about.

818
01:01:50,160 --> 01:01:51,160
So, I...

819
01:02:01,960 --> 01:02:03,600
Oh. Oh, I...

820
01:02:04,400 --> 01:02:05,600
I brought you something...

821
01:02:06,920 --> 01:02:08,520
to...

822
01:02:09,200 --> 01:02:11,800
keep you safe in the ring.

823
01:02:14,640 --> 01:02:17,200
Your mother would've
wanted you to have it.

824
01:02:18,080 --> 01:02:19,800
Wow. Thanks.

825
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:21,720
It's half of her breastplate.

826
01:02:23,600 --> 01:02:24,640
Matching set.

827
01:02:25,280 --> 01:02:26,280
Keeps her...

828
01:02:27,760 --> 01:02:29,120
It keeps her close, you know?

829
01:02:31,440 --> 01:02:32,920
Wear it proudly, son.

830
01:02:33,320 --> 01:02:35,640
You've held up your end of the deal.

831
01:02:42,080 --> 01:02:44,000
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Tired.

832
01:02:44,080 --> 01:02:46,520
- Yeah, I'm gonna get some sleep.
- Good talk.

833
01:02:46,600 --> 01:02:48,656
- Big day tomorrow.
- Yeah. Just... The Trial of Flame

834
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:51,096
- and it takes a lot out of you.
- Yeah, Trial of Flames... Flame.

835
01:02:51,120 --> 01:02:52,216
- Good luck with that.
- Yeah, thank you, thank you

836
01:02:52,240 --> 01:02:53,896
- I hope you like the...
- for the... the breast hat.

837
01:02:53,920 --> 01:02:55,520
- Hat. Yeah.
- Yeah.

838
01:02:56,720 --> 01:02:59,120
Okay, well, good night.

839
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:09,160
No more of your tricks.

840
01:03:09,240 --> 01:03:11,000
I'm taking Top Slayer today.

841
01:03:11,080 --> 01:03:13,720
Yeah, yeah, okay. It's all yours.
Top... Top Slay away.

842
01:03:14,680 --> 01:03:15,680
Sorry.

843
01:03:36,480 --> 01:03:38,440
Last chance. Make it count.

844
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:46,000
Come on!

845
01:03:46,080 --> 01:03:47,120
Go on, Astrid!

846
01:03:47,200 --> 01:03:48,800
- You got it! Go on!
- Come on, Hiccup!

847
01:03:48,880 --> 01:03:49,920
Come on!

848
01:03:54,640 --> 01:03:55,640
No!

849
01:03:56,000 --> 01:03:58,280
Son of a half-troll, rat-eating...

850
01:03:58,360 --> 01:04:00,000
Glad to see
she's handling it gracefully.

851
01:04:00,280 --> 01:04:01,280
You!

852
01:04:06,760 --> 01:04:07,760
Okay.

853
01:04:07,840 --> 01:04:09,720
- Later.
- Hey, hey. Not so fast.

854
01:04:09,800 --> 01:04:11,256
No, I can't. I'm gonna be late for...

855
01:04:11,280 --> 01:04:13,000
What? Late for what, exactly?

856
01:04:13,080 --> 01:04:14,320
- Another year,
- Shut up.

857
01:04:14,400 --> 01:04:17,120
And another Trial of Flame
has come to an end.

858
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:20,520
Elder Gothi has made her decision.

859
01:04:22,600 --> 01:04:27,120
The new Top Slayer will be...

860
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:42,600
Hiccup?

861
01:04:48,880 --> 01:04:50,120
You've done it, Hiccup.

862
01:04:50,200 --> 01:04:51,600
You won the Trial of Flame.

863
01:04:51,920 --> 01:04:53,120
You get to kill the dragon!

864
01:04:53,280 --> 01:04:54,600
That's my boy!

865
01:04:59,080 --> 01:05:01,240
Hiccup, you won!

866
01:05:04,360 --> 01:05:05,360
Yeah.

867
01:05:06,080 --> 01:05:07,200
Hooray me.

868
01:05:07,400 --> 01:05:09,200
I can't wait to...

869
01:05:09,280 --> 01:05:11,000
Beat it and never come back.

870
01:05:11,400 --> 01:05:12,720
All right, bud. Time's up.

871
01:05:13,760 --> 01:05:15,000
My thoughts exactly.

872
01:05:15,480 --> 01:05:16,640
What are you...

873
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:18,400
What are you doing here?

874
01:05:18,720 --> 01:05:20,000
Looking for answers.

875
01:05:20,760 --> 01:05:21,920
What are you doing here?

876
01:05:22,200 --> 01:05:23,520
Who's bud? Your trainer?

877
01:05:23,880 --> 01:05:25,000
Did he dress you up in this?

878
01:05:25,880 --> 01:05:28,640
I know this looks suspicious
but funnily enough, I...

879
01:05:29,640 --> 01:05:31,480
You're right! You're right. I...

880
01:05:31,560 --> 01:05:33,720
I'm through with the lies.
I've been making outfits

881
01:05:33,800 --> 01:05:36,240
so you got me.
It's time everybody knew.

882
01:05:36,320 --> 01:05:37,320
Just take me back.

883
01:05:39,280 --> 01:05:40,360
Why would you do that?

884
01:05:40,440 --> 01:05:41,760
That's for the lies.

885
01:05:43,160 --> 01:05:45,560
And that's for everything else.

886
01:05:47,760 --> 01:05:48,760
Oh, no.

887
01:05:49,480 --> 01:05:51,080
Run. Run!

888
01:05:51,160 --> 01:05:52,600
- No! No.
- What...

889
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:55,000
Toothless, no! Stop. It's okay.

890
01:05:55,400 --> 01:05:57,320
She's a friend. She's a friend.

891
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:04,320
Toothless, Astrid. Astrid, Toothless.

892
01:06:04,960 --> 01:06:05,960
The...

893
01:06:06,800 --> 01:06:07,800
The Night Fury.

894
01:06:13,560 --> 01:06:14,560
I wouldn't.

895
01:06:19,360 --> 01:06:20,360
We're dead.

896
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:25,000
Hey. Where do you think you're going?

897
01:06:54,840 --> 01:06:57,520
Hiccup! Get me down from here!

898
01:06:57,600 --> 01:06:59,056
You have to give me
a chance to explain.

899
01:06:59,080 --> 01:07:01,280
I'm not listening
to anything you have to say.

900
01:07:01,360 --> 01:07:02,400
Then I won't speak.

901
01:07:03,120 --> 01:07:04,120
Just let us show you.

902
01:07:04,960 --> 01:07:06,720
Please, Astrid.

903
01:07:18,160 --> 01:07:19,280
What is this?

904
01:07:20,720 --> 01:07:21,760
It's my design.

905
01:07:22,600 --> 01:07:24,320
Yeah. Pretty much the co-captain.

906
01:07:27,240 --> 01:07:28,600
Then let's get this over with.

907
01:07:29,880 --> 01:07:30,880
You got it.

908
01:07:31,440 --> 01:07:33,720
Toothless, let's take her down.

909
01:07:35,200 --> 01:07:36,200
Gently.

910
01:07:37,680 --> 01:07:38,680
Nothing to be afraid of.

911
01:07:46,000 --> 01:07:47,040
Oh, nice touch!

912
01:07:50,600 --> 01:07:52,240
I thought you were his co-captain!

913
01:07:52,320 --> 01:07:54,680
I am! It's a temporary
dragon malfunction!

914
01:07:58,160 --> 01:08:00,120
We worked out
a whole system, remember?

915
01:08:01,880 --> 01:08:04,320
If we survive, I'm gonna kill you!

916
01:08:08,720 --> 01:08:10,320
And now the spinning!

917
01:08:10,720 --> 01:08:13,520
Thank you for nothing,
you useless reptile.

918
01:08:13,600 --> 01:08:15,600
Please just make it stop.

919
01:08:17,720 --> 01:08:19,920
I'm clearly not the one in control!

920
01:08:20,160 --> 01:08:21,320
Then I'm sorry!

921
01:08:21,960 --> 01:08:23,720
Toothless, I'm sorry!

922
01:10:02,120 --> 01:10:03,120
Fine.

923
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:06,320
You made your point.

924
01:10:09,000 --> 01:10:11,440
It doesn't change the fact
you have to kill one tomorrow.

925
01:10:13,880 --> 01:10:14,976
But if we can change your mind...

926
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:16,000
What?

927
01:10:16,080 --> 01:10:18,040
You gonna take everyone up
for a magical ride?

928
01:10:21,400 --> 01:10:24,120
It won't erase
what they've done to us, Hiccup.

929
01:10:25,200 --> 01:10:27,000
They hunt us, steal our food.

930
01:10:27,080 --> 01:10:28,400
And one of them took my mom.

931
01:10:29,080 --> 01:10:30,376
But do we just keep
killing one another?

932
01:10:30,400 --> 01:10:31,680
As opposed to...

933
01:10:33,240 --> 01:10:34,240
I don't know.

934
01:10:36,080 --> 01:10:38,440
But you botched our escape plan,
so I'm gonna need a minute.

935
01:10:42,920 --> 01:10:46,120
Well, I might not snitch on you.

936
01:10:47,440 --> 01:10:49,520
And we might not drop you in the sea.

937
01:10:53,520 --> 01:10:55,320
Bud? What's up?

938
01:10:56,240 --> 01:10:57,240
What is it?

939
01:10:57,760 --> 01:10:58,800
Hey. Hey.

940
01:11:01,720 --> 01:11:02,720
Get down!

941
01:11:05,120 --> 01:11:06,680
Toothless, get us out of here.

942
01:11:12,720 --> 01:11:14,440
It looks like
they're hauling in their kill.

943
01:11:15,640 --> 01:11:17,000
Then what does that make us?

944
01:11:52,480 --> 01:11:53,840
The dragons' nest.

945
01:11:54,880 --> 01:11:57,240
Oh, what my dad wouldn't give
to find this.

946
01:12:30,040 --> 01:12:31,480
What is that?

947
01:12:34,320 --> 01:12:35,840
All right, bud, time to go.

948
01:12:44,880 --> 01:12:47,120
I can't believe it took
this long to figure it out.

949
01:12:47,560 --> 01:12:48,920
It all makes sense now.

950
01:12:49,360 --> 01:12:51,520
It's like a giant beehive.

951
01:12:51,840 --> 01:12:53,920
They're the workers,
and that's their queen.

952
01:12:54,120 --> 01:12:55,160
Their alpha.

953
01:12:55,240 --> 01:12:56,440
It controls them.

954
01:12:57,480 --> 01:12:58,480
We gotta find your dad.

955
01:12:58,560 --> 01:12:59,640
No, no, no, not yet.

956
01:13:00,200 --> 01:13:01,200
They'll...

957
01:13:01,520 --> 01:13:02,720
They'll kill Toothless.

958
01:13:04,440 --> 01:13:05,440
Astrid

959
01:13:06,000 --> 01:13:08,520
we have to think
this through carefully.

960
01:13:10,680 --> 01:13:13,800
Hiccup, we just discovered
the dragons' nest

961
01:13:14,600 --> 01:13:16,120
and you want to keep it a secret?

962
01:13:16,480 --> 01:13:18,600
To protect your pet dragon?

963
01:13:19,680 --> 01:13:20,880
Are you serious?

964
01:13:22,320 --> 01:13:23,320
Yes.

965
01:13:32,800 --> 01:13:33,800
Okay.

966
01:13:35,520 --> 01:13:37,720
Then what do we do?

967
01:13:41,840 --> 01:13:43,240
Just give me until tomorrow.

968
01:13:43,800 --> 01:13:44,800
I'll figure it out.

969
01:13:48,680 --> 01:13:50,000
That's for kidnapping me.

970
01:13:50,600 --> 01:13:51,640
Hey, are you gonna...

971
01:13:54,560 --> 01:13:57,240
And that's for everything else.

972
01:14:07,800 --> 01:14:08,800
What?

973
01:14:19,880 --> 01:14:24,000
Well, I can finally show
my face in public again!

974
01:14:27,960 --> 01:14:28,960
All right.

975
01:14:29,280 --> 01:14:30,920
If someone had told me

976
01:14:31,320 --> 01:14:33,000
that in a few short weeks

977
01:14:33,440 --> 01:14:37,600
Hiccup would've gone
from being, well, Hiccup...

978
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:43,240
to placing first
in the Trial of Flame

979
01:14:43,320 --> 01:14:46,040
I mean, I would've tied them
to a mast and shipped them off

980
01:14:46,120 --> 01:14:47,760
for fear they'd gone mad.

981
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:50,080
And you know it.

982
01:14:53,400 --> 01:14:54,480
But here we are.

983
01:14:56,640 --> 01:15:00,120
My son has won
the title of Top Slayer.

984
01:15:01,520 --> 01:15:03,600
No one is more surprised...

985
01:15:06,720 --> 01:15:09,200
or more proud than I am.

986
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:15,240
Today, my boy becomes a warrior.

987
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:20,120
Today, he becomes one of us!

988
01:15:20,200 --> 01:15:23,360
Yeah!

989
01:15:23,440 --> 01:15:24,480
Yeah!

990
01:15:25,680 --> 01:15:26,680
Yeah!

991
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:28,920
Yeah!

992
01:15:29,720 --> 01:15:37,680
Hiccup!

993
01:15:37,760 --> 01:15:44,800
Hiccup!

994
01:15:44,880 --> 01:15:45,880
Hiccup!

995
01:15:45,960 --> 01:15:47,320
Watch out for that dragon.

996
01:15:49,440 --> 01:15:51,040
It's not the dragon
I'm worried about.

997
01:15:54,480 --> 01:15:55,600
Look

998
01:15:55,680 --> 01:15:56,936
I'm gonna try
to put an end to all this

999
01:15:56,960 --> 01:15:58,720
but if something goes wrong
in there, just...

1000
01:16:00,840 --> 01:16:01,840
don't get involved.

1001
01:16:02,520 --> 01:16:04,000
My dad respects you too much.

1002
01:16:09,120 --> 01:16:10,120
Yeah.

1003
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:11,800
But...

1004
01:16:12,720 --> 01:16:14,400
you have something I don't.

1005
01:16:15,400 --> 01:16:18,320
Something none of us have.

1006
01:16:20,080 --> 01:16:21,080
So...

1007
01:16:21,840 --> 01:16:23,280
I'm going to stand by you...

1008
01:16:24,760 --> 01:16:25,800
come what may.

1009
01:16:29,200 --> 01:16:30,320
Come what may.

1010
01:16:32,640 --> 01:16:33,640
It's time, Hiccup.

1011
01:16:37,240 --> 01:16:38,320
Knock him dead, son.

1012
01:16:48,960 --> 01:16:56,760
Hiccup!

1013
01:16:56,880 --> 01:17:04,760
Hiccup!

1014
01:17:04,840 --> 01:17:07,000
Hiccup!

1015
01:17:07,080 --> 01:17:08,080
Go, Hiccup!

1016
01:17:08,160 --> 01:17:10,160
Show 'em everything I taught you!

1017
01:17:10,240 --> 01:17:11,360
Should've been me.

1018
01:17:13,760 --> 01:17:14,760
All right?

1019
01:17:15,200 --> 01:17:16,280
Good crowd, isn't it?

1020
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:22,000
Hiccup!

1021
01:17:35,320 --> 01:17:36,456
I would have gone with the hammer.

1022
01:17:36,480 --> 01:17:38,600
Just... Just give him a chance.

1023
01:17:46,280 --> 01:17:47,280
I'm ready.

1024
01:18:51,200 --> 01:18:52,400
What is he doing?

1025
01:18:54,840 --> 01:18:56,200
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1026
01:19:04,880 --> 01:19:06,040
I'm not one of them.

1027
01:19:19,560 --> 01:19:20,760
Stop the fight.

1028
01:19:20,840 --> 01:19:21,840
No.

1029
01:19:22,120 --> 01:19:23,640
You all need to see this.

1030
01:19:24,480 --> 01:19:26,000
They're not what we think they are.

1031
01:19:27,600 --> 01:19:28,920
We don't have to kill them.

1032
01:19:30,440 --> 01:19:32,800
I said stop the fight!

1033
01:19:39,720 --> 01:19:40,720
Out of my way!

1034
01:19:41,840 --> 01:19:43,200
Get out of there, Hiccup!

1035
01:19:44,840 --> 01:19:45,840
Hiccup!

1036
01:20:00,080 --> 01:20:01,080
No!

1037
01:20:05,760 --> 01:20:07,600
- Quick, quick! Grab his hand!
- Climb up!

1038
01:20:07,680 --> 01:20:09,176
- Hiccup, grab my hand!
- Get over here!

1039
01:20:09,200 --> 01:20:10,800
Get over here, man!
Just grab his hand!

1040
01:20:19,760 --> 01:20:21,520
Astrid, get back here!

1041
01:20:22,440 --> 01:20:23,720
That's an order!

1042
01:20:30,600 --> 01:20:31,680
Run!

1043
01:20:32,920 --> 01:20:33,920
Come on!

1044
01:20:36,320 --> 01:20:37,320
Hiccup!

1045
01:20:49,520 --> 01:20:50,520
Night Fury.

1046
01:20:51,160 --> 01:20:52,720
Night Fury!

1047
01:20:52,800 --> 01:20:54,080
He's real!

1048
01:21:02,720 --> 01:21:03,960
Night Fury!

1049
01:21:20,400 --> 01:21:22,080
All right, bud. Go on. Go.

1050
01:21:24,960 --> 01:21:26,840
Go, go! Get to the side of him!

1051
01:21:30,120 --> 01:21:31,400
Get out of the way, Hiccup!

1052
01:21:35,840 --> 01:21:37,320
No, stop.
You're only making it worse!

1053
01:21:39,480 --> 01:21:40,480
Astrid!

1054
01:21:43,960 --> 01:21:44,960
I got it. Go!

1055
01:21:47,280 --> 01:21:49,080
Stoick, he won't hurt you.

1056
01:21:54,560 --> 01:21:56,000
Get around it!

1057
01:21:58,920 --> 01:21:59,920
No!

1058
01:22:04,760 --> 01:22:05,760
Toothless!

1059
01:22:06,800 --> 01:22:07,800
Don't.

1060
01:22:11,000 --> 01:22:12,200
Take it down!

1061
01:22:14,480 --> 01:22:15,640
Grab its legs!

1062
01:22:16,080 --> 01:22:18,040
- Hold it down!
- No! No, don't hurt him!

1063
01:22:18,120 --> 01:22:19,640
Stay back!

1064
01:22:25,160 --> 01:22:26,160
And you.

1065
01:22:39,440 --> 01:22:40,680
Put it with the others.

1066
01:22:47,360 --> 01:22:48,480
- I should have known!
- Dad.

1067
01:22:48,560 --> 01:22:49,976
- I should have seen the signs.
- Dad!

1068
01:22:50,000 --> 01:22:52,200
- We had a deal!
- I know, but that was before...

1069
01:22:52,760 --> 01:22:54,120
It's all so messed up.

1070
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:58,680
So everything in the ring,
what, a trick? A lie?

1071
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:01,040
No, I should have told you
before now.

1072
01:23:01,520 --> 01:23:02,880
Take that out on me, it's my fault

1073
01:23:02,920 --> 01:23:04,320
but please don't hurt Toothless.

1074
01:23:05,920 --> 01:23:07,000
The dragon?

1075
01:23:08,040 --> 01:23:09,680
That's what you're worried about?

1076
01:23:10,400 --> 01:23:12,200
Not the people you almost killed?

1077
01:23:12,280 --> 01:23:14,400
He's not dangerous.
He was protecting me.

1078
01:23:14,480 --> 01:23:17,520
They took your mother,
for Gods' sake!

1079
01:23:19,160 --> 01:23:22,440
If she could see you now
standing there with them

1080
01:23:22,520 --> 01:23:24,200
when they've killed hundreds of us.

1081
01:23:24,280 --> 01:23:25,920
And we've killed thousands of them!

1082
01:23:26,440 --> 01:23:28,000
They defend themselves. That's all.

1083
01:23:28,520 --> 01:23:30,200
They raid us because they have to.

1084
01:23:30,280 --> 01:23:31,416
If they don't bring enough food back

1085
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:32,680
they'll be eaten themselves!

1086
01:23:33,320 --> 01:23:34,840
There's something else
on their island.

1087
01:23:34,880 --> 01:23:36,320
A dragon like I've never seen.

1088
01:23:36,400 --> 01:23:37,400
Their island?

1089
01:23:39,960 --> 01:23:41,200
You've been to the nest.

1090
01:23:42,040 --> 01:23:43,040
Did I say nest?

1091
01:23:44,080 --> 01:23:45,640
How did you find it?

1092
01:23:45,720 --> 01:23:47,520
I didn't. Toothless did.

1093
01:23:47,760 --> 01:23:49,520
Only a dragon can find the island.

1094
01:23:53,040 --> 01:23:55,720
No. Dad, no.

1095
01:23:56,040 --> 01:23:57,096
You don't know
what you're up against.

1096
01:23:57,120 --> 01:23:58,600
This is nothing like
you've ever seen.

1097
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:01,040
You can't win this one!

1098
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:04,360
For once in your life,
would you please just listen to me?

1099
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:10,920
You've thrown your lot in with them.

1100
01:24:12,600 --> 01:24:13,920
You're not one of us.

1101
01:24:14,600 --> 01:24:15,920
You're not my son.

1102
01:24:25,600 --> 01:24:26,800
Ready the ships!

1103
01:24:27,320 --> 01:24:28,720
We sail at dawn!

1104
01:24:51,360 --> 01:24:53,280
Dragon to the port side!

1105
01:24:56,720 --> 01:24:58,440
Forward on the leading line!

1106
01:24:58,520 --> 01:24:59,800
Swing it out slightly!

1107
01:24:59,880 --> 01:25:01,520
Here she comes! Easy!

1108
01:25:02,000 --> 01:25:03,120
Careful with the head.

1109
01:25:04,160 --> 01:25:06,280
- One more.
- Oh, careful now.

1110
01:25:06,360 --> 01:25:08,120
- Hey.
- Weapons loaded!

1111
01:25:08,480 --> 01:25:09,760
Spare rigging aboard?

1112
01:25:09,840 --> 01:25:12,000
- Aye.
- Hoist the sails!

1113
01:25:12,080 --> 01:25:13,080
Aye, Chief.

1114
01:25:16,120 --> 01:25:18,000
- Ready the oars.
- Aye, Stoick.

1115
01:25:19,520 --> 01:25:22,400
We set sail for Helheim's Gate!

1116
01:25:39,000 --> 01:25:41,000
Lead us home, devil.

1117
01:26:10,400 --> 01:26:11,720
I tried to stop them.

1118
01:26:12,880 --> 01:26:14,800
I ended up giving them
exactly what they wanted.

1119
01:26:18,320 --> 01:26:19,400
I should've just...

1120
01:26:20,720 --> 01:26:22,880
I should've killed him
when I found him in those woods.

1121
01:26:25,240 --> 01:26:26,760
It would have been
better for everyone.

1122
01:26:27,360 --> 01:26:28,360
Yeah.

1123
01:26:28,720 --> 01:26:30,080
The rest of us would have done it.

1124
01:26:33,400 --> 01:26:34,520
So, why didn't you?

1125
01:26:35,680 --> 01:26:36,736
- Why didn't you?
- I don't know.

1126
01:26:36,760 --> 01:26:38,200
- I couldn't.
- That's not an answer.

1127
01:26:38,240 --> 01:26:40,056
Why is this so important
to you all of a sudden?

1128
01:26:40,080 --> 01:26:42,200
Because I want to remember
what you say right now.

1129
01:26:42,280 --> 01:26:44,120
For the love of...
Because I was weak.

1130
01:26:44,480 --> 01:26:46,496
Because I was a coward,
because I wouldn't kill a dragon.

1131
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:48,720
- You said "wouldn't" that time.
- Whatever! I wouldn't!

1132
01:26:49,320 --> 01:26:51,760
I'm the first Viking
in who knows how long

1133
01:26:51,840 --> 01:26:53,120
who wouldn't kill a dragon.

1134
01:26:55,200 --> 01:26:56,760
First to ride one, though.

1135
01:27:03,160 --> 01:27:04,160
So?

1136
01:27:07,880 --> 01:27:09,320
I wouldn't kill him because...

1137
01:27:11,400 --> 01:27:13,200
he looked
just as frightened as I was.

1138
01:27:16,680 --> 01:27:17,800
When I looked at him...

1139
01:27:19,600 --> 01:27:20,920
I saw myself.

1140
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:32,800
Bet he's really frightened now.

1141
01:27:39,720 --> 01:27:41,200
What are you gonna do about it?

1142
01:27:43,720 --> 01:27:45,200
Probably something stupid.

1143
01:27:47,360 --> 01:27:48,600
Well, you've already done that.

1144
01:27:54,360 --> 01:27:55,360
Then something crazy.

1145
01:27:57,040 --> 01:27:58,520
That's more like it.

1146
01:28:04,440 --> 01:28:05,920
Sound your positions.

1147
01:28:06,200 --> 01:28:07,680
Stay within earshot.

1148
01:28:08,400 --> 01:28:10,120
One length to your stern.

1149
01:28:10,200 --> 01:28:11,720
On your starboard flank.

1150
01:28:12,200 --> 01:28:14,280
Why aren't they attacking?

1151
01:28:14,800 --> 01:28:16,480
Maybe they know something we don't.

1152
01:28:19,840 --> 01:28:21,536
Are you just a glutton
for punishment or what?

1153
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:23,800
We have a fighting chance this time.

1154
01:28:25,880 --> 01:28:27,080
Thanks to Hiccup.

1155
01:28:28,400 --> 01:28:29,800
How long do you think we're gonna...

1156
01:28:40,960 --> 01:28:42,280
Step aside, Drül.

1157
01:28:57,640 --> 01:28:59,600
- Ship the oars!
- Oars in.

1158
01:29:13,560 --> 01:29:14,560
Okay, wait.

1159
01:29:14,680 --> 01:29:18,000
You just disgraced yourself
in front of the whole village.

1160
01:29:18,400 --> 01:29:20,296
- Why would we listen to you?
- 'Cause I said so.

1161
01:29:20,320 --> 01:29:22,440
Exactly. Pay attention, gang.

1162
01:29:22,520 --> 01:29:25,360
Look, my dad means well,
but he's stubborn.

1163
01:29:25,640 --> 01:29:28,000
And he's about to be way in
over his head, so it's up to us.

1164
01:29:28,200 --> 01:29:29,200
Us?

1165
01:29:29,480 --> 01:29:31,160
I can't pull this off
without you guys.

1166
01:29:31,600 --> 01:29:33,320
And you all have
something special to offer.

1167
01:29:33,560 --> 01:29:34,560
Say no more.

1168
01:29:35,040 --> 01:29:38,120
You were wise to seek
the world's most deadly weapon.

1169
01:29:38,800 --> 01:29:40,240
- It's me.
- You've got a wild side

1170
01:29:40,320 --> 01:29:41,320
and I like it.

1171
01:29:41,560 --> 01:29:43,960
Astrid, you're our strongest fighter.
We need you to lead us.

1172
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:45,880
Lead us where exactly?

1173
01:29:45,960 --> 01:29:48,440
They left with every ship we have.

1174
01:29:51,200 --> 01:29:52,240
Stick with me.

1175
01:29:58,600 --> 01:29:59,920
That's where that went.

1176
01:30:00,000 --> 01:30:01,000
Stay low.

1177
01:30:01,680 --> 01:30:02,680
Be ready.

1178
01:30:40,400 --> 01:30:41,520
We're here.

1179
01:30:59,080 --> 01:31:00,080
No.

1180
01:31:01,440 --> 01:31:03,400
Hiccup, I...

1181
01:31:04,440 --> 01:31:05,480
Relax.

1182
01:31:08,320 --> 01:31:09,320
It's okay.

1183
01:31:20,360 --> 01:31:21,400
Where are you going?

1184
01:31:21,840 --> 01:31:23,720
You're gonna need something
to help you hold on.

1185
01:31:24,080 --> 01:31:25,080
Get ready.

1186
01:31:25,760 --> 01:31:26,840
It's gonna be a long night.

1187
01:31:34,280 --> 01:31:36,240
Form a defensive line.

1188
01:31:41,440 --> 01:31:43,840
Sharpen those axes, lads!

1189
01:31:47,520 --> 01:31:48,640
It's not even.

1190
01:31:51,920 --> 01:31:52,920
Chief.

1191
01:31:53,840 --> 01:31:54,840
Ready, Chief.

1192
01:31:56,800 --> 01:31:58,800
- Stand strong.
- Aye, Stoick.

1193
01:32:00,200 --> 01:32:01,560
Make your people proud.

1194
01:32:01,640 --> 01:32:02,920
We will, Stoick.

1195
01:32:05,120 --> 01:32:09,640
Today, we destroy
the reign of the dragon

1196
01:32:09,720 --> 01:32:11,000
once and for all.

1197
01:32:15,600 --> 01:32:19,320
However this ends,
it ends right here, right now!

1198
01:32:21,000 --> 01:32:24,280
So let's send these devils
back to hell!

1199
01:33:38,960 --> 01:33:39,960
Is that it?

1200
01:33:40,840 --> 01:33:42,120
The nest is ours!

1201
01:33:45,920 --> 01:33:47,200
This isn't over.

1202
01:33:55,640 --> 01:33:56,880
Get clear!

1203
01:33:57,440 --> 01:33:58,960
Fall back!

1204
01:33:59,040 --> 01:34:01,000
Fall back! Everyone, fall back!

1205
01:34:06,960 --> 01:34:07,960
Retreat!

1206
01:34:38,640 --> 01:34:40,640
Get to the ships!

1207
01:34:41,040 --> 01:34:42,120
No!

1208
01:34:54,960 --> 01:34:56,416
Get them
to the far side of the island!

1209
01:34:56,440 --> 01:34:58,200
Aye, Chief. Let's move!

1210
01:34:58,280 --> 01:35:00,480
This way! All of you!

1211
01:35:05,840 --> 01:35:07,720
- Get out of here, lads!
- Follow me!

1212
01:35:07,920 --> 01:35:09,480
Gobber, go with the others.

1213
01:35:09,560 --> 01:35:11,600
Why? Where are you going?

1214
01:35:19,320 --> 01:35:20,840
Actually, I'm gonna stick around.

1215
01:35:20,920 --> 01:35:22,600
You've got
that wild look in your eye.

1216
01:35:23,560 --> 01:35:25,080
I can buy them some time

1217
01:35:25,160 --> 01:35:27,160
if I give that thing
something to hunt.

1218
01:35:27,240 --> 01:35:28,800
And I can double that time.

1219
01:35:29,880 --> 01:35:31,640
I know. I'm a big softy.

1220
01:35:32,360 --> 01:35:35,000
Softest part of you is your teeth.

1221
01:36:03,760 --> 01:36:06,880
Remember, that thing is their queen.

1222
01:36:06,960 --> 01:36:08,560
They're inclined
to do whatever it says.

1223
01:36:09,000 --> 01:36:10,320
We've gotta help them fight back.

1224
01:36:12,880 --> 01:36:14,600
Fishlegs, what do we got?

1225
01:36:15,520 --> 01:36:17,400
Heavily armored skull and tail

1226
01:36:17,480 --> 01:36:19,360
perfect for bashing and crushing.

1227
01:36:19,640 --> 01:36:21,960
Small eyes, large nostrils.

1228
01:36:22,040 --> 01:36:23,600
Relies on hearing and smell.

1229
01:36:23,920 --> 01:36:25,440
Got it. Astrid.

1230
01:36:25,720 --> 01:36:29,400
Okay. Snotlout, Fishlegs,
hang in its blind spot.

1231
01:36:29,480 --> 01:36:31,600
Make some noise. Keep it confused.

1232
01:36:32,200 --> 01:36:34,600
Ruff, Tuff, figure out
its shot limit.

1233
01:36:34,680 --> 01:36:35,760
Make it mad.

1234
01:36:35,840 --> 01:36:37,600
That's our specialty!

1235
01:36:39,560 --> 01:36:41,200
Try not to get killed, guys!

1236
01:36:51,840 --> 01:36:54,000
This thing doesn't have a blind spot.

1237
01:36:57,560 --> 01:36:58,560
There!

1238
01:37:04,760 --> 01:37:05,760
Hey, bud.

1239
01:37:06,520 --> 01:37:07,560
I'm... I'm good.

1240
01:37:07,640 --> 01:37:08,720
Be careful.

1241
01:37:13,800 --> 01:37:15,880
I know, I know,
but I'm... I'm here now.

1242
01:37:28,720 --> 01:37:29,920
Keep hammering!

1243
01:37:30,160 --> 01:37:32,400
But we're confusing our own dragons!

1244
01:37:32,800 --> 01:37:34,000
Oh, no!

1245
01:37:41,560 --> 01:37:43,760
This way! This way! Come on! Come on!

1246
01:37:43,840 --> 01:37:45,056
Guys, keep moving! Keep moving!

1247
01:37:45,080 --> 01:37:46,200
- Come on!
- Go!

1248
01:37:46,280 --> 01:37:47,640
Is that my kid?

1249
01:37:48,040 --> 01:37:50,400
- Snotlout!
- Come on! Throw it!

1250
01:37:52,920 --> 01:37:54,000
Whoa, girl.

1251
01:37:54,920 --> 01:37:56,040
Going down!

1252
01:37:58,960 --> 01:37:59,960
I'm okay.

1253
01:38:01,320 --> 01:38:02,360
Less okay.

1254
01:38:05,800 --> 01:38:07,480
I got you, Fishlegs!

1255
01:38:15,320 --> 01:38:16,480
What's wrong?

1256
01:38:16,560 --> 01:38:18,320
Got something in your eye?

1257
01:38:19,400 --> 01:38:22,200
Yeah! Now, that's a Top Slayer.

1258
01:39:39,000 --> 01:39:40,000
You got it, bud.

1259
01:39:46,120 --> 01:39:47,120
Hiccup.

1260
01:39:49,920 --> 01:39:51,840
I was only trying to protect you.

1261
01:39:52,920 --> 01:39:54,000
I know, Dad.

1262
01:39:55,200 --> 01:39:56,480
Let me return the favor.

1263
01:39:59,520 --> 01:40:01,000
Whatever happens up there

1264
01:40:01,600 --> 01:40:04,760
I'm proud to call you my son.

1265
01:40:09,160 --> 01:40:10,400
And that's all I need.

1266
01:40:12,200 --> 01:40:13,200
Let's go.

1267
01:40:17,480 --> 01:40:18,480
He's up!

1268
01:40:19,800 --> 01:40:21,400
You two get Snotlout.

1269
01:40:21,720 --> 01:40:23,000
I'll distract the queen.

1270
01:40:25,200 --> 01:40:27,600
That's right. Eyes on me.

1271
01:40:29,880 --> 01:40:31,000
Snotlout!

1272
01:40:34,760 --> 01:40:35,760
Now!

1273
01:40:36,000 --> 01:40:37,760
Oh, you have gotta be kidding me.

1274
01:40:51,000 --> 01:40:52,600
I can't believe that worked.

1275
01:40:53,200 --> 01:40:54,200
Yeah.

1276
01:40:57,000 --> 01:40:58,440
No, no, no, girl.

1277
01:40:59,240 --> 01:41:01,440
Fight it! Don't listen to her!

1278
01:41:01,640 --> 01:41:02,720
Shake it off!

1279
01:41:26,440 --> 01:41:27,440
Astrid.

1280
01:41:43,360 --> 01:41:44,360
Did you get her?

1281
01:41:57,800 --> 01:41:58,800
Go.

1282
01:42:01,800 --> 01:42:03,000
That thing has wings.

1283
01:42:03,720 --> 01:42:04,960
Let's see if it can use them.

1284
01:42:19,960 --> 01:42:21,120
You think that did it?

1285
01:42:24,040 --> 01:42:25,040
Yep.

1286
01:42:39,960 --> 01:42:41,800
All right, bud.
It's time to disappear.

1287
01:42:47,840 --> 01:42:49,520
Here it comes!

1288
01:42:55,800 --> 01:42:57,600
Quite the chief you have
in the making there.

1289
01:42:58,160 --> 01:42:59,160
Aye.

1290
01:43:39,080 --> 01:43:40,080
Watch out!

1291
01:43:43,800 --> 01:43:45,040
Okay, time's up.

1292
01:43:45,320 --> 01:43:46,480
Let's see if this works.

1293
01:43:52,200 --> 01:43:53,600
Is that all you've got?

1294
01:44:12,080 --> 01:44:13,320
Stay with me, bud!

1295
01:44:13,720 --> 01:44:15,120
Just a little bit longer!

1296
01:44:16,600 --> 01:44:17,800
Hold, Toothless!

1297
01:44:20,760 --> 01:44:21,760
Now!

1298
01:44:42,600 --> 01:44:44,720
Yeah, bud, we... No!

1299
01:45:03,480 --> 01:45:04,600
Hiccup!

1300
01:45:09,520 --> 01:45:10,640
Hiccup?

1301
01:45:11,720 --> 01:45:12,840
Son?

1302
01:45:14,960 --> 01:45:16,320
Hiccup!

1303
01:45:31,000 --> 01:45:32,120
Oh, son.

1304
01:45:44,560 --> 01:45:46,000
I'm so sorry.

1305
01:46:55,840 --> 01:46:56,840
Hiccup.

1306
01:47:04,800 --> 01:47:05,800
He's alive.

1307
01:47:06,320 --> 01:47:07,320
He's alive!

1308
01:47:10,000 --> 01:47:11,360
Yeah!

1309
01:47:12,360 --> 01:47:13,360
Yes!

1310
01:47:23,880 --> 01:47:25,240
Thank you...

1311
01:47:26,600 --> 01:47:28,240
for saving my son.

1312
01:47:30,160 --> 01:47:32,800
Well, you know, most of him.

1313
01:47:48,200 --> 01:47:49,400
Hey, Toothless.

1314
01:47:51,600 --> 01:47:52,600
Okay.

1315
01:47:58,160 --> 01:47:59,480
I'm in my house.

1316
01:48:01,560 --> 01:48:03,000
You're in my house.

1317
01:48:03,520 --> 01:48:05,000
Does my dad know you're here?

1318
01:48:06,480 --> 01:48:07,480
Come on.

1319
01:48:53,960 --> 01:48:54,960
Thanks, bud.

1320
01:48:58,880 --> 01:49:00,040
Okay, here we go.

1321
01:49:29,120 --> 01:49:31,360
Toothless, stay.

1322
01:49:34,440 --> 01:49:37,000
Hey! Shouldn't you be in bed?

1323
01:49:38,480 --> 01:49:40,680
Okay. Hold on tight, guys.

1324
01:49:41,480 --> 01:49:42,480
Here we go.

1325
01:49:51,840 --> 01:49:53,840
Hey! Hey! There you go!

1326
01:49:59,320 --> 01:50:01,520
- There he is!
- Okay.

1327
01:50:03,360 --> 01:50:04,520
So, what do you think?

1328
01:50:05,720 --> 01:50:07,400
A few changes since you've been out.

1329
01:50:08,160 --> 01:50:11,320
Flying back here was
quite an experience

1330
01:50:11,400 --> 01:50:12,920
- let me tell you.
- Wait, wait, you...

1331
01:50:13,320 --> 01:50:14,480
you rode a dragon?

1332
01:50:14,560 --> 01:50:17,360
Well... Well, that monster burned
all of our ships, so...

1333
01:50:17,440 --> 01:50:19,216
- Hiccup!
- We didn't really have much of a...

1334
01:50:19,240 --> 01:50:21,320
Oh, no. What'd I do this time?

1335
01:50:22,520 --> 01:50:24,160
- Ow!
- That's for scaring me.

1336
01:50:24,240 --> 01:50:26,120
Okay, is it always gonna
be like this? 'Cause...

1337
01:50:30,160 --> 01:50:32,200
And that's for everything else.

1338
01:50:32,680 --> 01:50:35,000
You know, 'cause...
'cause I... I could get used to that.

1339
01:50:35,960 --> 01:50:37,000
Yep.

1340
01:50:37,080 --> 01:50:41,320
Turns out all we needed
was a little more of this.

1341
01:50:42,120 --> 01:50:43,640
You just gestured to all of me.

1342
01:50:44,040 --> 01:50:46,280
Well, you know, most of ya.

1343
01:50:47,040 --> 01:50:48,320
New leg is my handiwork

1344
01:50:48,400 --> 01:50:51,520
with just a dash of your kooky flair
thrown in for good measure.

1345
01:50:52,200 --> 01:50:54,240
Here we go. Welcome home.

1346
01:50:54,320 --> 01:50:55,600
- You rebuilt it?
- Yeah.

1347
01:50:55,680 --> 01:50:56,920
I found your designs.

1348
01:50:57,640 --> 01:50:58,640
Not too bad.

1349
01:50:59,440 --> 01:51:00,440
Night Fury!

1350
01:51:01,960 --> 01:51:03,160
- Here he is.
- What is it?

1351
01:51:03,440 --> 01:51:04,880
What is it, huh?

1352
01:51:04,960 --> 01:51:06,120
Want to take it for a spin?

1353
01:51:17,240 --> 01:51:19,160
<i>This is Berk.</i>

1354
01:51:21,400 --> 01:51:23,200
<i>You'd have to be crazy to move here.</i>

1355
01:51:25,000 --> 01:51:26,920
<i>Even crazier to stay.</i>

1356
01:51:29,000 --> 01:51:30,840
<i>It's not for the faint of heart.</i>

1357
01:51:37,160 --> 01:51:40,200
<i>Any food that grows here
is tough and tasteless.</i>

1358
01:51:41,080 --> 01:51:42,080
Come on!

1359
01:51:43,280 --> 01:51:44,640
<i>The people that grow here</i>

1360
01:51:45,280 --> 01:51:46,440
<i>are even more so.</i>

1361
01:51:49,520 --> 01:51:52,000
<i>The only upsides are the pets.</i>

1362
01:51:52,960 --> 01:51:56,520
<i>While other places may have
ponies or puppies...</i>

1363
01:51:56,600 --> 01:51:57,680
Come on, bud.

1364
01:51:57,760 --> 01:51:58,760
<i>We have...</i>

1365
01:52:01,880 --> 01:52:02,960
<i>dragons.</i>

